records.addlTxt:
8:51 AM Defendant Zachary M Lobotzke in court. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe. 
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Defendant chooses to proceed without an attorney after doing a consultation with an attorney. Court conducts colloquy and finds Defendant waives right to an attorney freely, voluntarily, and intelligently.
State places offer on the record. 
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty. 
State makes sentencing recommendations. 

Court orders the following:
IMPOSED AND STAYED: 

JAIL:  90 Days in the Waukesha County Jail w/Huber (all standard release conditions).
0  Days Credit.

TERM ON PROBATION:  12 MONTHS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No (violent) contact with:  E.K.; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State-certified batterer's intervention program with an Anger Management component; 
*Completion of a Parenting class; 

DOMESTIC VIOLENCE SURCHARGE:  $100;
COSTS:  $243
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.
